 &lt;p&gt;‚≠êÔ∏è‚≠êÔ∏è&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;&#34;&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=&#34;https://leetcode.com/problems/optimal-partition-of-string/&#34;&gt;&lt;ins class=&#34;dot&#34;&gt;È°åÁõÆÊïòËø∞&lt;/ins&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Given a string  &lt;code&gt;s&lt;/code&gt; , partition the string into one or more &lt;strong&gt;substrings&lt;/strong&gt; such that the characters in each substring are &lt;strong&gt;unique&lt;/strong&gt;. That is, no letter appears in a single substring more than &lt;strong&gt;once&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Return the &lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;minimum&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt; number of substrings in such a partition.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Note that each character should belong to exactly one substring in a partition.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;example-1&#34;&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#example-1&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt; Example 1:&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Input:&lt;/strong&gt; s = &amp;quot;abacaba&amp;quot;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Output:&lt;/strong&gt; 4&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Explanation:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
Two possible partitions are (&amp;quot;a&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;ba&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;cab&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;a&amp;quot;) and (&amp;quot;ab&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;a&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;ca&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;ba&amp;quot;).&lt;br /&gt;
It can be shown that 4 is the minimum number of substrings needed.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;example-2&#34;&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#example-2&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt; Example 2:&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Input:&lt;/strong&gt; s = &amp;quot;ssssss&amp;quot;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Output:&lt;/strong&gt; 6&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Explanation:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
The only valid partition is (&amp;quot;s&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;s&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;s&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;s&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;s&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;s&amp;quot;).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
